autoexec.scriptcontenttips:
Help:
Get the parameter value by the parameter name, such as:
print $inputParam1
Set the return value by assigning the output parameter, such as:
my $outParam1="outParam1-Value"
 Input parameters: 
 Text and Password parameters can obtain a string representing the actual value
 Node parameters can obtain an IP
 File parameters can obtain the file name, and the storage address is in The current execution directory.
Output parameters:
Text type parameters can output text in any format
Report data:
Define the parameter named: report_json, the value needs to be in legal json format.
Exit code identification :
As long as the ExitCode is not equal to 0, it means abnormal exit.
Note:
If you need to initiate a child process, please pay attention to close the standard output and error output after execution, otherwise the parent process may not exit normally.
